The Twitch thing got so many men thinking. So many people thinking. Reminding us life is hard af. But we should also be reminded that that’s ok. Life IS hard. But life is also beautiful and fulfilling. I am fortunate to have a job. I’m fortunate to be able to drop off my wife at work, my kids at daycare. I’m happy I get to grab my favorite skillet at one of my favorite breakfast spots in the city. See this morning has been great…so far, in the evening things could change or tomorrow, life could take a turn for the worse. When it does, you know what, it’s ok. Life won’t be great every day nor will it be consistently shitty. Give yourself some grace through the hard…this is a reminder to show yourself a little love today (or ditch everyone and go get a skillet from cozy corner)

I often tell Nicole that I love her more than I love Whitney and Wriley. And while I know I’m 3rd place in HER heart, it is without question she occupies the most space in mine. From the very beginning she has accepted me with all my flaws and baggage. Things I can’t even write about on here. The first day I met her I called @pinqy.ring and told her I found my SUPERBAE. Funny that despite it being a pretty awesome nickname, it wouldn’t do her justice. WIFE is superior. MOMMY has a better ring to it. BEST FRIEND (sorry Hector & 3RUM2) captures who she is to me. Thank you for dealing with me, the angry cookie aka the grumpy lump. I love you deeply and appreciate who you are to me and this family 💟
